expression: text
---
Recover the chunk tree by scanning the device for surviving chunk data.

Sweeps the raw device for tree blocks that belong to the chunk tree, extracts
CHUNK_ITEM and DEV_ITEM records, resolves conflicts between duplicates found at
different generations, and reports whether a coherent chunk tree can be
reconstructed.

By default this is a read-only scan that reports whether recovery is possible.
Use --apply to actually write the reconstructed chunk tree.

Usage: chunk-recover [OPTIONS] <DEVICE>

Arguments:
  <DEVICE>
          Device to recover

Options:
  -y, --yes
          Assume an answer of 'yes' to all questions

      --apply
          Write the reconstructed chunk tree to disk

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
